Aluminum metal samples with diameter equal to the
various lead samples and thickness of 50 - 300 micro-

The lead samples were sandwiched in layers between
aluminum monitor foils for the cross section determi-
nations. Also, auxiliary aluminum, iron, nickel,
indium, and niobium samples were used at various times
during these experiments, either to serve as secondary
standards for neutron fluence determination or for
the purpose of establishing corrections for low-energy
neutrons via the method of spectral indexing.
Cross sections were measured using the neutron
activation method. Packets containing various lead
samples and monitor foils were irradiated in well-
defined geometries near the target of the accelerator.
All sample activities were measured by obser-
